    <abstract>
      <t>The EDNS(0) Extension Mechanism for DNS is explicitly defined to only have "per-message" semantics. This document defines a new Session Signaling Opcode used to communicate persistent "per-session" operations, expressed using type-length-value (TLV) syntax, and defines an initial set of TLVs used to manage session timeouts and termination.</t>
